===Etymology===
Coined by EW Barton-Wright in 1899, from ‘Bart(on-Wright)’ + [[jujitsu]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/bɑ:'tɪtsu:/}}

===Noun===
'''Bartitsu'''
# a form of [[martial arts]] combining [[boxing]], [[savate]], [[ju-jitsu]] and [[stick fighting]], popularized by E.W. Barton-Wright in London during the late-Victorian era.

